        "content": "<p>I couldn't figure out how to use it, e.g.:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">[[</span><span class=\"n\">lean_exe</span><span class=\"o\">]]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Main.*\"</span>\n<span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"Main.*\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>blows up:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">lakefile</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">toml</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">25</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">7</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">expected</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">name</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The problem presumably is that it can't match <code>name</code> and <code>root</code> one by one, it would just expand both to all files.</p>\n<p><code>globs</code> itself does not seem to be a valid optoin to <code>lean_exe</code>: <a href=\"https://lean-lang.org/doc/reference/latest/Build-Tools-and-Distribution/Lake/#Lake___LeanExeConfig\">https://lean-lang.org/doc/reference/latest/Build-Tools-and-Distribution/Lake/#Lake___LeanExeConfig</a></p>",
